text: Sadriddin Saymatov (born 28 July 1997) is an Uzbekistani karateka. In 2018, he won one of the bronze medals in the men's kumite 60 kg event at the 2018 Asian Games held in Jakarta, Indonesia. In 2019, at the 2019 Asian Karate Championships held in Tashkent, Uzbekistan he won the gold medal in the men's kumite 60 kg event. == References == == External links == * Category:Living people Category:1997 births Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Uzbekistani male karateka Category:Karateka at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Asian Games medalists in karate Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for Uzbekistan Category:Asian Games competitors for Uzbekistan
